In 2014, we launched the Workflow4Metabolomics  (W4M;  http://workflow4metabolomics.org) online infrastructure for metabolomics built on the  Galaxy enviro nment, which offers user-friendly features  to build and run data analysis  workflows including preprocessing, statistical analysis, and annotation steps.
Raw files (in the open NetCDF format) are  publicly available on W4M ( http://workflow4metabolomics.org/datasets ).
The converted files from the W4M00004 study are available  for download from W4M as a unique zipped file (260.8 MB ;  http://workflow4metabolomics.org/datasets) .
TopSpin (Bruker) preprocessed files (Bruker format) are available on  W4M for download ( http://workflow4metabolomics.org/datasets ).
